\r\n	"supervisor" : "Bond",\r\n	"supervisorEmail" : "james@mi6.co.uk"\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\nThis works without having to define data types for these fields or create new tables and table definitions for clearance supervisors, or create a new schema.\r\n\r\nSchemaless JSON allows developers to store relevant information efficiently in a single document, and modify the document as they wish according to changing application requirements, or a changing reality. With a schemaless database such as Clusterpoint, developers are free to focus on getting the most out of their data, instead of wrangling it all into a single schema.\r\n\r\nTo find out more on SQL syntax, check out our documentation for <a href="https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/?version=3" target="_blank">Clusterpoint 3</a> and <a href="https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/?version=4" target="_blank">Clusterpoint 4</a>', 'Migrating Beyond The Schema: Schemaless JSON Documents', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'migrating-beyond-the-schema-schemaless-json-documents', '', '', '2016-02-02 14:16:44', '2016-02-02 12:16:44', '', 0, 'https://newwww.clusterpoint.com/wp/?p=88', 8, 'post', '', 0),
