(815, 119, '_faqs_3_text', 'field_56b9dec5432c3'),
(816, 119, 'faqs_4_title', 'Are database version 3 and 4 APIs mutually compatible?'),
(817, 119, '_faqs_4_title', 'field_56b9debe432c2'),
(818, 119, 'faqs_4_text', 'No. Database version 4 introduces new API language, that combines 2 of the most popular IT concepts: SQL and JavaScript. As a result – it’s incompatible with XML based API language that was used in older Clusterpoint DB versions 2 and 3.\r\nYou can compare version 3 and version 4 APIs in our API Documentation at: <a href="https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/api/4/rest">https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/api/4/rest</a>'),
(819, 119, '_faqs_4_text', 'field_56b9dec5432c3'),
(820, 119, 'faqs_5_title', 'Can I import my MySQL database into Clusterpoint Cloud DB?'),
(821, 119, '_faqs_5_title', 'field_56b9debe432c2'),
(822, 119, 'faqs_5_text', 'Yes – you should export each MySQL database table as an XML or .CSV document, and then import them through Cloud DB Management Web Console at <a href="https://cloud.clusterpoint.com">https://cloud.clusterpoint.com</a>'),
(823, 119, '_faqs_5_text', 'field_56b9dec5432c3'),
(824, 119, 'faqs_6_title', 'When do I need to Reindex my database?'),
(825, 119, '_faqs_6_title', 'field_56b9debe432c2'),
(826, 119, 'faqs_6_text', 'In general – the only scenario when you need to reindex your database is, then you have changed your database Data Model. For more info check <a href="https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/4.0/378/database-data-model">https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/4.0/378/database-data-model</a>'),
(827, 119, '_faqs_6_text', 'field_56b9dec5432c3'),
(828, 119, 'faqs_7_title', 'Do you have geospatial search functionality?'),
(829, 119, '_faqs_7_title', 'field_56b9debe432c2'),
(830, 119, 'faqs_7_text', 'Clusterpoint can handle various data and has special features for working with geospatial information. More information on this here: <a href="https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/4.0/1/where#toc-geospatial-search">https://www.clusterpoint.com/docs/4.0/1/where#toc-geospatial-search</a>'),
(831, 119, '_faqs_7_text', 'field_56b9dec5432c3'),
